<item>
            <title>[AMQ-1654] Mirror Topics for temorary queues</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-1654</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when Mirror queues are enabled AMQ is creating mirror queues for all the temp queues created to fulfill the transactions. But when temp queues are removed by the broker because the transaction is complete, the Mirror queues/topics are still there, they should be removed as well. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There should be a configuration setting to turn on/ turn off mirror topic/queues support for temp queues. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There got to be some overhead in AMQ to maintain a lot of mirror queues for temporary queues where there are millions of transaction.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;AMQ 5.0 / 5.1 SNAPSHOT on Solaris 10&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
